webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Interior of Torpa Church in Östergötland. Performed in stone around 1460, it replaced a former church building of timber. From this 1200th century church, parts of a baptismal funt and three sculptures have been preserved, namely triumphal crucifix, an St. King’s image and an St. Stephen’s. The small altar of the church is painted by Gottfrid Hentschel after a Dutch painting from the 16th century - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000293. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419839. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
